reviews.text: Nice food and reasonably priced. The dumpling selection is good.
Too cheap and teate not good

This used to be good several years ago now it's just another local Chinese restaurant. Food selection is shanghainese style mainly. 
Typical tightly packed crowded restaurant at all times, not enough space for large groups over 8 people. 
The dumplings I had were so hard it's unbelievable they can sell this. Rest of the food was average tasting too for me.
ok,good!

It provides several vegetarian noodles and dishes.  Vegetarians can eat Shanghai style dishes here but not only Guangdong dishes.  The price is acceptable but not low.  The dining environment is good as it is spacious and comfortable.  It's not only provide noodles but main dishes at lunch and dinner times.
